org.jcvi.jillion.core

Class Range.Builder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.core.Range.Builder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Rangeable
    Enclosing class:
    Range

    public static final class Range.Builder
extends Object
implements Rangeable
    Builder is a mutable object that allows clients to create a Range object using the current specification.

    Note: build() is not guaranteed to return new instances and may return a cached instance instead (flyweight pattern).

    This class is not thread-safe.

    Author:
    dkatzel

        public Builder(long begin,
               long end)
        Create a new Builder instance which is initialized to the given begin and end coordinates in zero-based coordinate space. This is equivalent to new Builder(CoordinateSystem.ZERO_BASED, begin,end).
        Parameters:
        begin - the initial inclusive begin coordinate of the range in zero based coordinates.
        end - the initial inclusive end coordinate in zero based coordinates.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the given begin and end coordiantes cause the length to be negative.

      • Builder

               long begin,
               long end)
        Create a new Builder instance which is initialized to the given begin and end coordinates in the given coordinate space.
        Parameters:
        cs - the Range.CoordinateSystem these coordinates are given in; can not be null.
        begin - the initial begin coordinate of the range in the given Range.CoordinateSystem.
        end - the initial end coordinate of the range in the given Range.CoordinateSystem.

        NullPointerException - if cs is null.

    • Method Detail

      • shift

        public Range.Builder shift(long units)
        Shift the entire range by the given amount of units. Both the begin and end coordinates will be adjusted by the given value. The length will remain the same.
        Parameters:
        units - the amount to shift. If this number is positive, then the begin and end coordinates will be increased; if this number is negative, then the begin and end coordinates will be decreased. A value of 0 will cause no changes.
        Returns:
        this.

      • contractBegin

        public Range.Builder contractBegin(long units)
        Shrink the begin value by the given amount of units. This will add the given number of units to the begin coordinate which will also cause the range's length to be shrunk by the given amount.
        Parameters:
        units - the amount to shrink to the left. If this number is negative, then that is the equivalent of growing to the left by the given number of units
        Returns:
        this.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if shrinking the begin coordinate by the given amount causes the range's length to be negative.
        See Also:
        expandBegin(long)

      • contractEnd

        public Range.Builder contractEnd(long units)
        Shrink the end value by the given amount of units. This will subtract the given number of units to the end coordinate which will also cause the range's length to be shrunk by the given amount.
        Parameters:
        units - the amount to shrink to the right. If this number is negative, then that is the equivalent of growing to the right by the given number of units
        Returns:
        this.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if shrinking the end coordinate by the given amount causes the range's length to be negative.
        See Also:
        expandEnd(long)

      • build

        public Range build()
        Use the current begin, end and length values of this Builder to return an instance of a Range object with the same values. This method is not guaranteed to return new instances and may return a cached instance instead (flyweight pattern).
        Returns:
        a Range; never null but might not be a new instance.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if end &lt; begin -1 or if the resulting range length > Long.MAX_VALUE.
